## Introduction
This chapter guides you through your first steps right after starting Doxee Template Designer for the very first time.

## Step by Step
Running *Doxee Template Designer *for the first time, you start with an empty window. In order to get to your first *Infinica Template*, you have to create a new one. Click the toolbar icon *New Template ![](data:image/png;base64,)* and select *Template *in the upcoming dialog. Instead of using the toolbar, you could also use the menu *File &gt; New Template *or just press *CTRL+N *in order to get to that dialog. Select a destination for your new template, define any name you like, e.g. my first template.itx and confirm it. *Infinica Templates *are saved using the extension ITX. The figure below shows the perspective you start with in a new template.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*Figure 1. Empty Template*

Place the cursor in the Design Window. Type Hello World! Save the changes via the menu *File &gt; Save *or by using the according toolbar icon  ![](data:image/png;base64,). Open the view *Properties *via the menu *View &gt; Properties *and apply the following settings:

**Custom font size**

You can apply font sizes via the toolbar as well as using the view *Properties &gt; Font &gt; Font Size *or *Advanced &gt; Fonts &gt; font size*. Values can be entered using pt and metric units, too. Additionally it is possible to use the predefined font size settings. Either select the text to apply the font size on in the *Design *Window or select the paragraph to apply settings on in the *Outline View *and choose a font size.

**Custom font colour**

Set the font colour using Properties &gt; Font or Advanced &gt; Colors &gt; color. The default colour is black. Select the text to apply the colour to in the Design Window or in the Outline View and choose some font colour.

**Font style bold**

This can be done using the toolbar ![](data:image/png;base64,) or in *Properties &gt; Font *or *Advanced &gt; Fonts &gt; font weight*. Select the text to apply the style to in the Design Window or in the *Outline View *and choose font style bold. Font style bold is a property that is inherited.

**Underlined text**

Select the text to apply the style to in the Design Window or in the *Outline View *and choose *underline ![](data:image/png;base64,)* in the toolbar or apply *Properties &gt; Advanced &gt; Character &gt; text- decoration: *underline. This property can only be applied to text elements and is not inherited.

**Custom background colour**

First decide if the background shall be set to some text or to the whole paragraph (Block). Choose some text section or the whole *Block *element, containing the *Text *element, in the *Outline View *and apply any background colour using *Properties &gt; Font *or *Advanced&gt; Border, Padding and Background &gt; background-color*.

Click on the tab *PDF (FOP) *in the *Designer *Window, in order to create a preview document.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*Figure 2. PDF Preview*

## Things to Try
- Create a new template and enter some paragraphs of text

- Experiment with text and block formatting

- Explore the *Palette*, which can be found on the right side of the *Design *Window (if the *Palette *is not visible, see [Introduction](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-template-designer-user-guide-images-1#introduction))

- Open Views via the View Menu and explore them. After opening views they can be placed arbitrarily. More information about the different views can be found in the *Doxee Template Designer User Guide*.
